## Permission Structure

Proxmox uses a path-based permission system:

- **/** - Root path (cluster-wide permissions)
- **/nodes/{node}** - Node-specific permissions
- **/vms/{vmid}** - VM-specific permissions
- **/storage/{storage}** - Storage-specific permissions
- **/pool/{pool}** - Resource pool permissions

## Built-in Roles

Common Proxmox roles:

- **Administrator**: Full access to all resources
- **PVEAdmin**: Can do most administrative tasks except user management
- **PVEVMAdmin**: Full VM administration
- **PVEVMUser**: Can use VMs (start/stop/console)
- **PVEAuditor**: Read-only access
- **PVEDatastoreAdmin**: Storage administration
- **PVEDatastoreUser**: Allocate disk space, view storage
- **PVEPoolAdmin**: Pool administration
- **PVEPoolUser**: Use resources in pool
- **PVESysAdmin**: System administration (not VM management)
- **PVEUserAdmin**: User and authentication management

